description.details:
Study a short section of audio and estimate its tempo, assuming the tempo is constant
Code copyright 2008 Queen Mary, University of London.  Freely redistributable (BSD license)
description.name: Simple Fixed Tempo Estimator

parameters.description: Minimum beat-per-minute value which the tempo estimator is able to return
parameters.name: Minimum estimated tempo

parameters.description: Maximum beat-per-minute value which the tempo estimator is able to return
parameters.name: Maximum estimated tempo

parameters.description: Length of audio input, in seconds, which should be taken into account when estimating tempo.  There is no need to supply the plugin with any further input once this time has elapsed since the start of the audio.  The tempo estimator may use only the first part of this, up to eight times the slowest beat duration: increasing this value further than that is unlikely to improve results.
parameters.name: Input duration to study
